This paper presents a machine learning pipeline for program analysis, which is a subfield of software engineering (cs.SE). The focus of the paper is on security analysis, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and symbolic rules suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of existing techniques and proposes possible improvements, which could be related to machine learning (cs.LG).
